{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896504529,"sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","part":{"id":"prt_d7bae28a100173GtfAt1v40iZq","messageID":"msg_d7bae133b001U1q8ONuj1CXdnU","sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_tool-335222043fcf4f5497d3238df2c06c79","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"**/agentcube/**/*.go"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/agentcube/main.go","metadata":{"count":1,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z","time":{"start":1775896504514,"end":1775896504528}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896504553,"sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","part":{"id":"prt_d7bae27bf001TlqphL2mN4JOLY","messageID":"msg_d7bae133b001U1q8ONuj1CXdnU","sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c979eb16bcbd4f59991b9875c7dffd7c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document outlines the technical implementation of comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube project. The E2E test suite validates the complete system behavior by deploying a real or simulated Kubernetes environment, creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, and verifying end-to-end workflows including session creation, invocation, routing, and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `test/e2e`  \n8: **Language:** Go  \n9: **Source Root:** `/test/e2e/`  \n10: **Size:** L  \n11: **Dependencies:** client-go, kind/minikube/k3s, Ginkgo/Gomega\n12: \n13: ## Architecture\n14: \n15: ### E2E Test Architecture\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                    E2E Test Framework                       │\n20: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n21: │  │           Test Execution Layer                        │  │\n22: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n23: │  │  │  Ginkgo Test Suite                             │  │  │\n24: │  │  │  • Test Organization (Describe/Context/It)     │  │  │\n25: │  │  │  • Lifecycle Hooks (BeforeSuite/AfterSuite)   │  │  │\n26: │  │  │  • Parallel Execution Support                 │  │  │\n27: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n28: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n29: │                           │                                  │\n30: │                           ▼                                  │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n32: │  │           Kubernetes Environment Layer                │  │\n33: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n34: │  │  │  Environment Setup (kind/minikube/k3s)         │  │  │\n35: │  │  │  • Cluster Provisioning                       │  │  │\n36: │  │  │  • AgentCube Deployment                        │  │  │\n37: │  │  │  • Resource Cleanup                           │  │  │\n38: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n39: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n40: │  │  │  Environment Interface                        │  │  │\n41: │  │  │  • Kubeconfig Management                      │  │  │\n42: │  │  │  • Client Configuration                       │  │  │\n43: │  │  │  • Namespace Management                       │  │  │\n44: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n45: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n46: │                           │                                  │\n47: │                           ▼                                  │\n48: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n49: │  │           Test Helpers & Utilities Layer             │  │\n50: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n51: │  │  │  Resource Assertions                          │  │  │\n52: │  │  │  • CRD Creation Verification                  │  │  │\n53: │  │  │  • Pod Status Checking                        │  │  │\n54: │  │  │  • Service Endpoint Verification              │  │  │\n55: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n56: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n57: │  │  │  HTTP Client Utilities                        │  │  │\n58: │  │  │  • Request/Response Validation                │  │  │\n59: │  │  │  • Timeout Handling                           │  │  │\n60: │  │  │  • Retry Logic                               │  │  │\n61: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n62: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n63: │  │  │  Data Generators                              │  │  │\n64: │  │  │  • Sample AgentRuntime Specs                  │  │  │\n65: │  │  │  • Sample CodeInterpreter Specs               │  │  │\n66: │  │  │  • Test Payload Generators                    │  │  │\n67: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n68: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n69: │                           │                                  │\n70: │                           ▼                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n72: │           System Under Test (SUT)                         │\n73: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n74: │  │  AgentRuntime CRDs  │  CodeInterpreter CRDs          │  │\n75: │  │  workload-manager   │  router                        │  │\n76: │  │  session-store      │  picod                         │  │\n77: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n78: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ### Test Categories\n82: \n83: ```\n84: test/e2e/\n85: ├── agentruntime/                    # AgentRuntime E2E tests\n86: │   ├── agentruntime_suite_test.go  # Main test suite\n87: │   ├── creation_test.go            # Creation workflow tests\n88: │   ├── invocation_test.go          # Invocation workflow tests\n89: │   ├── lifecycle_test.go           # Lifecycle management tests\n90: │   └── error_handling_test.go      # Error scenario tests\n91: ├── codeinterpreter/                # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\n92: │   ├── codeinterpreter_suite_test.go\n93: │   ├── creation_test.go\n94: │   ├── execution_test.go\n95: │   ├── file_operations_test.go\n96: │   └── error_handling_test.go\n97: ├── integration/                    # Cross-component tests\n98: │   ├── workflow_test.go            # End-to-end workflow tests\n99: │   ├── routing_test.go             # Routing integration tests\n100: │   ├── session_management_test.go  # Session lifecycle tests\n101: │   └── scalability_test.go         # Load and stress tests\n102: ├── framework/                      # Test framework code\n103: │   ├── framework.go                # Core framework setup\n104: │   ├── helpers.go                  # Common test helpers\n105: │   ├── assertions.go               # Custom assertions\n106: │   └── fixtures.go                 # Test fixtures\n107: └── manifests/                      # Test manifests\n108:     ├── agentruntimes/              # AgentRuntime test manifests\n109:     ├── codeinterpreters/           # CodeInterpreter test manifests\n110:     └── deployments/                # Deployment configurations\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## Data Structures\n114: \n115: ### Framework Configuration\n116: \n117: **File**: `test/e2e/framework/framework.go`\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: // TestFramework provides the core E2E test framework\n121: type TestFramework struct {\n122:     // Client configuration\n123:     config      *rest.Config\n124:     clientset   *kubernetes.Clientset\n125:     agentClient *agentclient.Clientset\n126:     \n127:     // Test environment\n128:     namespace   string\n129:     clusterName string\n130:     \n131:     // HTTP client for service endpoints\n132:     httpClient *http.Client\n133:     \n134:     // Test state\n135:     cleanup     []func() error\n136: }\n137: \n138: // FrameworkOptions provides configuration for TestFramework\n139: type FrameworkOptions struct {\n140:     // Namespace is the test namespace (default: e2e-test-<random>)\n141:     Namespace string\n142:     \n143:     // ClusterName identifies the cluster (for multi-cluster tests)\n144:     ClusterName string\n145:     \n146:     // Timeout is the default timeout for operations (default: 5m)\n147:     Timeout time.Duration\n148:     \n149:     // PollInterval is the default poll interval (default: 1s)\n150:     PollInterval time.Duration\n151:     \n152:     // SkipCleanup skips resource cleanup after tests (default: false)\n153:     SkipCleanup bool\n154: }\n155: \n156: // NewDefaultFramework creates a framework with default options\n157: func NewDefaultFramework(name string) *TestFramework {\n158:     return NewFramework(name, FrameworkOptions{})\n159: }\n160: \n161: // NewFramework creates a test framework with custom options\n162: func NewFramework(name string, opts FrameworkOptions) *TestFramework\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### Test Helpers\n166: \n167: **File**: `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go`\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: // AgentRuntimeHelper provides utilities for AgentRuntime E2E tests\n171: type AgentRuntimeHelper struct {\n172:     framework *TestFramework\n173: }\n174: \n175: // NewAgentRuntimeHelper creates a new AgentRuntime helper\n176: func NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f *TestFramework) *AgentRuntimeHelper\n177: \n178: // CreateAgentRuntime creates an AgentRuntime resource\n179: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) CreateAgentRuntime(\n180:     ctx context.Context,\n181:     agent *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime,\n182: ) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n183: \n184: // GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime resource\n185: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) GetAgentRuntime(\n186:     ctx context.Context,\n187:     name string,\n188: ) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n189: \n190: // WaitForAgentRuntimeReady waits for AgentRuntime to be ready\n191: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(\n192:     ctx context.Context,\n193:     name string,\n194:     timeout time.Duration,\n195: ) error\n196: \n197: // CreateSession creates a session via workload-manager API\n198: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) CreateSession(\n199:     ctx context.Context,\n200:     req *api.CreateSandboxRequest,\n201: ) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n202: \n203: // InvokeSession invokes a session via router\n204: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) InvokeSession(\n205:     ctx context.Context,\n206:     sessionID string,\n207:     payload []byte,\n208:     headers map[string]string,\n209: ) (*api.InvokeResponse, error)\n210: \n211: // DeleteSession deletes a session\n212: func (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) DeleteSession(\n213:     ctx context.Context,\n214:     sessionID string,\n215: ) error\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### CodeInterpreter Helpers\n219: \n220: ```go\n221: // CodeInterpreterHelper provides utilities for CodeInterpreter E2E tests\n222: type CodeInterpreterHelper struct {\n223:     framework *TestFramework\n224: }\n225: \n226: // NewCodeInterpreterHelper creates a new CodeInterpreter helper\n227: func NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f *TestFramework) *CodeInterpreterHelper\n228: \n229: // CreateCodeInterpreter creates a CodeInterpreter resource\n230: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) CreateCodeInterpreter(\n231:     ctx context.Context,\n232:     ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter,\n233: ) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n234: \n235: // GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter resource\n236: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) GetCodeInterpreter(\n237:     ctx context.Context,\n238:     name string,\n239: ) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n240: \n241: // WaitForCodeInterpreterReady waits for CodeInterpreter to be ready\n242: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(\n243:     ctx context.Context,\n244:     name string,\n245:     timeout time.Duration,\n246: ) error\n247: \n248: // ExecuteCode executes code in a CodeInterpreter session\n249: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) ExecuteCode(\n250:     ctx context.Context,\n251:     sessionID string,\n252:     code string,\n253: ) (*api.ExecuteResponse, error)\n254: \n255: // UploadFile uploads a file to a CodeInterpreter session\n256: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) UploadFile(\n257:     ctx context.Context,\n258:     sessionID string,\n259:     filename string,\n260:     content []byte,\n261: ) error\n262: \n263: // DownloadFile downloads a file from a CodeInterpreter session\n264: func (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) DownloadFile(\n265:     ctx context.Context,\n266:     sessionID string,\n267:     filename string,\n268: ) ([]byte, error)\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ### Assertions\n272: \n273: **File**: `test/e2e/framework/assertions.go`\n274: \n275: ```go\n276: // EventuallyWithTimeout provides Gomega's Eventually with custom timeout\n277: func EventuallyWithTimeout(\n278:     actual interface{},\n279:     timeout time.Duration,\n280:     intervals ...interface{},\n281: ) AsyncAssertion\n282: \n283: // ConsistentlyWithTimeout provides Gomega's Consistently with custom timeout\n284: func ConsistentlyWithTimeout(\n285:     actual interface{},\n286:     timeout time.Duration,\n287:     intervals ...interface{},\n288: ) AsyncAssertion\n289: \n290: // HaveConditions verifies conditions match\n291: func HaveConditions(expected ...metav1.Condition) OmegaMatcher\n292: \n293: // BeReady verifies resource is ready\n294: func BeReady() OmegaMatcher\n295: \n296: // HavePhase verifies resource phase\n297: func HavePhase(phase string) OmegaMatcher\n298: \n299: // HaveEndpoint verifies endpoint is accessible\n300: func HaveEndpoint(endpoint string) OmegaMatcher\n301: \n302: // ReturnSuccess verifies HTTP call succeeds\n303: func ReturnSuccess() OmegaMatcher\n304: \n305: // ReturnStatusCode verifies HTTP status code\n306: func ReturnStatusCode(code int) OmegaMatcher\n307: \n308: // HaveSessionID verifies response has session ID\n309: func HaveSessionID() OmegaMatcher\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ### Fixtures\n313: \n314: **File**: `test/e2e/framework/fixtures.go`\n315: \n316: ```go\n317: // NewTestAgentRuntime creates a test AgentRuntime with defaults\n318: func NewTestAgentRuntime(name string) *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n319: \n320: // NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec creates a test AgentRuntime with custom spec\n321: func NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec(\n322:     name string,\n323:     spec v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec,\n324: ) *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n325: \n326: // NewTestCodeInterpreter creates a test CodeInterpreter with defaults\n327: func NewTestCodeInterpreter(name string) *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n328: \n329: // NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec creates a test CodeInterpreter with custom spec\n330: func NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec(\n331:     name string,\n332:     spec v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec,\n333: ) *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n334: \n335: // NewTestSessionRequest creates a test session request\n336: func NewTestSessionRequest(kind, name, namespace string) *api.CreateSandboxRequest\n337: \n338: // NewTestInvokePayload creates a test invoke payload\n339: func NewTestInvokePayload(data map[string]interface{}) []byte\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ## API Contracts\n343: \n344: ### E2E Test Suite Structure\n345: \n346: **File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/agentruntime_suite_test.go`\n347: \n348: ```go\n349: package e2e\n350: \n351: import (\n352:     . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n353:     . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n354:     \n355:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n356:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/test/e2e/framework\"\n357: )\n358: \n359: var _ = Describe(\"AgentRuntime E2E\", func() {\n360:     var (\n361:         f       *framework.TestFramework\n362:         helper  *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper\n363:         ns      string\n364:     )\n365: \n366:     BeforeSuite(func() {\n367:         // Initialize framework\n368:         f = framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"agentruntime-e2e\")\n369:         \n370:         // Get or create namespace\n371:         ns = f.Namespace\n372:         \n373:         // Wait for AgentCube deployment to be ready\n374:         Eventually(func() bool {\n375:             return f.AgentCubeReady()\n376:         }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n377:         \n378:         // Initialize helper\n379:         helper = framework.NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f)\n380:     })\n381: \n382:     AfterSuite(func() {\n383:         if !f.Options.SkipCleanup {\n384:             f.Cleanup()\n385:         }\n386:     })\n387:     \n388:     // Test contexts will be included here\n389: })\n390: ```\n391: \n392: ### AgentRuntime Creation Tests\n393: \n394: **File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/creation_test.go`\n395: \n396: ```go\n397: var _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() {\n398:     It(\"should create AgentRuntime successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n399:         art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-creation\")\n400:         art.Namespace = ns\n401:         \n402:         // Create AgentRuntime\n403:         created, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n404:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n405:         Expect(created.Name).To(Equal(art.Name))\n406:         Expect(created.Namespace).To(Equal(ns))\n407:     }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n408: \n409:     It(\"should apply default values\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n410:         art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n411:             ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n412:                 Name:      \"test-defaults\",\n413:                 Namespace: ns,\n414:             },\n415:             Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n416:                 PodTemplate: runtimev1alpha1.PodTemplateSpec{\n417:                     Spec: runtimev1alpha1.PodSpec{\n418:                         Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.Container{\n419:                             {\n420:                                 Name:  \"agent\",\n421:                                 Image: \"nginx:latest\",\n422:                             },\n423:                         },\n424:                     },\n425:                 },\n426:             },\n427:         }\n428:         \n429:         created, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n430:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n431:         \n432:         // Verify defaults\n433:         Expect(created.Spec.MaxSessionDuration).To(Equal(\"8h\"))\n434:         Expect(created.Spec.SessionTimeout).To(Equal(\"15m\"))\n435:     }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n436: \n437:     It(\"should become ready\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n438:         art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-ready\")\n439:         art.Namespace = ns\n440:         \n441:         _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n442:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n443:         \n444:         // Wait for ready status\n445:         err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n446:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n447:         \n448:         // Verify status\n449:         fetched, err := helper.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, art.Name)\n450:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n451:         Expect(fetched.Status.Ready).To(BeTrue())\n452:     }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n453: })\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### AgentRuntime Invocation Tests\n457: \n458: **File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/invocation_test.go`\n459: \n460: ```go\n461: var _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Invocation\", func() {\n462:     var (\n463:         art       *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n464:         sessionID string\n465:     )\n466: \n467:     BeforeEach(func() {\n468:         // Create AgentRuntime\n469:         art = framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-invocation\")\n470:         art.Namespace = ns\n471:         \n472:         ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 2*time.Minute)\n473:         defer cancel()\n474:         \n475:         var err error\n476:         art, err = helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n477:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n478:         \n479:         // Wait for ready\n480:         err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n481:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n482:     })\n483: \n484:     It(\"should create session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n485:         req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n486:         \n487:         resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n488:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n489:         Expect(resp).NotTo(BeNil())\n490:         Expect(resp.SessionID).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n491:         \n492:         sessionID = resp.SessionID\n493:     }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n494: \n495:     It(\"should invoke session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n496:         // First create session\n497:         req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n498:         resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n499:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n500:         sessionID = resp.SessionID\n501:         \n502:         // Invoke session\n503:         payload := framework.NewTestInvokePayload(map[string]interface{}{\n504:             \"message\": \"hello\",\n505:         })\n506:         \n507:         invokeResp, err := helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, nil)\n508:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n509:         Expect(invokeResp.StatusCode).To(Equal(200))\n510:     }, SpecTimeout(3*time.Minute))\n511: \n512:     It(\"should handle concurrent invocations\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n513:         // Create session\n514:         req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n515:         resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n516:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n517:         sessionID = resp.SessionID\n518:         \n519:         // Concurrent invocations\n520:         var wg sync.WaitGroup\n521:         errors := make(chan error, 10)\n522:         \n523:         for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {\n524:             wg.Add(1)\n525:             go func() {\n526:                 defer wg.Done()\n527:                 payload := framework.NewTestInvokePayload(map[string]interface{}{\n528:                     \"id\": i,\n529:                 })\n530:                 _, err := helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, nil)\n531:                 errors <- err\n532:             }()\n533:         }\n534:         \n535:         wg.Wait()\n536:         close(errors)\n537:         \n538:         // Verify all invocations succeeded\n539:         for err := range errors {\n540:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n541:         }\n542:     }, SpecTimeout(5*time.Minute))\n543: })\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ### AgentRuntime Lifecycle Tests\n547: \n548: **File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/lifecycle_test.go`\n549: \n550: ```go\n551: var _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Lifecycle\", func() {\n552:     It(\"should handle session expiration\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n553:         // Create AgentRuntime with short session timeout\n554:         art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-expiration\")\n555:         art.Namespace = ns\n556:         art.Spec.SessionTimeout = \"30s\"\n557:         \n558:         _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n559:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n560:         \n561:         err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n562:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n563:         \n564:         // Create session\n565:         req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n566:         resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n567:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n568:         sessionID := resp.SessionID\n569:         \n570:         // Wait for expiration\n571:         time.Sleep(35 * time.Second)\n572:         \n573:         // Verify session is expired\n574:         _, err = helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, []byte(\"{}\"), nil)\n575:         Expect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n576:     }, SpecTimeout(7*time.Minute))\n577: \n578:     It(\"should delete session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n579:         art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-deletion\")\n580:         art.Namespace = ns\n581:         \n582:         _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n583:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n584:         \n585:         err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n586:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n587:         \n588:         // Create session\n589:         req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n590:         resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n591:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n592:         sessionID := resp.SessionID\n593:         \n594:         // Delete session\n595:         err = helper.DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID)\n596:         Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n597:         \n598:         // Verify session is deleted\n599:         _, err = helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, []byte(\"{}\"), nil)\n600:         Expect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n601:     }, SpecTimeout(8*time.Minute))\n602: })\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ### CodeInterpreter Execution Tests\n606: \n607: **File**: `test/e2e/codeinterpreter/execution_test.go`\n608: \n609: ```go\n610: var _ = Describe(\"CodeInterpreter E2E\", func() {\n611:     var (\n612:         f       *framework.TestFramework\n613:         helper  *framework.CodeInterpreterHelper\n614:         ns      string\n615:     )\n616: \n617:     BeforeSuite(func() {\n618:         f = framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"codeinterpreter-e2e\")\n619:         ns = f.Namespace\n620:         \n621:         Eventually(func() bool {\n622:             return f.AgentCubeReady()\n623:         }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n624:         \n625:         helper = framework.NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f)\n626:     })\n627: \n628:     AfterSuite(func() {\n629:         if !f.Options.SkipCleanup {\n630:             f.Cleanup()\n631:         }\n632:     })\n633: \n634:     Context(\"Code Execution\", func() {\n635:         It(\"should execute Python code successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n636:             ci := framework.NewTestCodeInterpreter(\"test-execution\")\n637:             ci.Namespace = ns\n638:             \n639:             _, err := helper.CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci)\n640:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n641:             \n642:             err = helper.WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, ci.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n643:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n644:             \n645:             // Create session and execute code\n646:             // (implementation depends on CodeInterpreter API)\n647:         }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n648: \n649:         It(\"should handle syntax errors\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n650:             ci := framework.NewTestCodeInterpreter(\"test-syntax-error\")\n651:             ci.Namespace = ns\n652:             \n653:             _, err := helper.CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci)\n654:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n655:             \n656:             err = helper.WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, ci.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n657:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n658:             \n659:             // Execute code with syntax error\n660:             // Verify error is returned\n661:         }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n662:     })\n663: })\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ## Error Handling\n667: \n668: ### Test Failure Handling\n669: \n670: ```go\n671: // TestFailureHandler provides error handling for test failures\n672: type TestFailureHandler struct {\n673:     framework *TestFramework\n674: }\n675: \n676: // OnFailure handles test failures by collecting diagnostics\n677: func (h *TestFailureHandler) OnFailure(failedSpec SpecReport) {\n678:     // Collect pod logs\n679:     h.collectPodLogs(failedSpec)\n680:     \n681:     // Collect resource status\n682:     h.collectResourceStatus(failedSpec)\n683:     \n684:     // Collect events\n685:     h.collectEvents(failedSpec)\n686:     \n687:     // Save diagnostics to file\n688:     h.saveDiagnostics(failedSpec)\n689: }\n690: \n691: func (h *TestFailureHandler) collectPodLogs(spec SpecReport) {\n692:     pods, err := h.framework.Clientset.CoreV1().Pods(h.framework.Namespace).List(\n693:         context.Background(),\n694:         metav1.ListOptions{},\n695:     )\n696:     if err != nil {\n697:         return\n698:     }\n699:     \n700:     for _, pod := range pods.Items {\n701:         logFile := fmt.Sprintf(\"logs/%s-%s.log\", spec.LeafNodeText, pod.Name)\n702:         \n703:         for _, container := range pod.Spec.Containers {\n704:             logs, err := h.framework.Clientset.CoreV1().Pods(h.framework.Namespace).GetLogs(\n705:                 pod.Name,\n706:                 &corev1.PodLogOptions{\n707:                     Container: container.Name,\n708:                 },\n709:             ).DoRaw(context.Background())\n710:             \n711:             if err == nil {\n712:                 os.WriteFile(logFile, logs, 0644)\n713:             }\n714:         }\n715:     }\n716: }\n717: ```\n718: \n719: ### Retry Logic\n720: \n721: ```go\n722: // Retryable provides retry logic for flaky operations\n723: func Retryable(\n724:     fn func() error,\n725:     maxRetries int,\n726:     backoff time.Duration,\n727: ) error {\n728:     var lastErr error\n729:     \n730:     for i := 0; i < maxRetries; i++ {\n731:         err := fn()\n732:         if err == nil {\n733:             return nil\n734:         }\n735:         \n736:         lastErr = err\n737:         time.Sleep(backoff * time.Duration(i+1))\n738:     }\n739:     \n740:     return lastErr\n741: }\n742: \n743: // EventuallyRetryable combines Gomega's Eventually with retry\n744: func EventuallyRetryable(\n745:     actual interface{},\n746:     timeout time.Duration,\n747:     pollingInterval time.Duration,\n748:     maxRetries int,\n749: ) AsyncAssertion {\n750:     return Eventually(\n751:         actual,\n752:         timeout,\n753:         pollingInterval,\n754:     ).WithPolling(pollingInterval).WithTimeout(timeout)\n755: }\n756: ```\n757: \n758: ### Timeout Management\n759: \n760: ```go\n761: // TimeoutContext creates a context with timeout and cancellation\n762: func TimeoutContext(timeout time.Duration) (context.Context, context.CancelFunc) {\n763:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), timeout)\n764:     \n765:     // Handle timeout\n766:     go func() {\n767:         <-ctx.Done()\n768:         if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n769:             fmt.Printf(\"Operation timed out after %v\\n\", timeout)\n770:         }\n771:     }()\n772:     \n773:     return ctx, cancel\n774: }\n775: \n776: // WithDefaultTimeout creates a context with default test timeout\n777: func WithDefaultTimeout() (context.Context, context.CancelFunc) {\n778:     return TimeoutContext(5 * time.Minute)\n779: }\n780: ```\n781: \n782: ## Testing Strategy\n783: \n784: ### Test Execution Strategy\n785: \n786: #### Unit-Level E2E Tests\n787: \n788: Test individual components in an integrated environment:\n789: \n790: ```go\n791: // Test AgentRuntime creation in isolation\n792: Context(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() {\n793:     It(\"should create AgentRuntime with valid spec\", func() {\n794:         // Test creation logic\n795:     })\n796: })\n797: ```\n798: \n799: #### Workflow-Level E2E Tests\n800: \n801: Test complete workflows across multiple components:\n802: \n803: ```go\n804: // Test complete pack -> build -> publish -> invoke workflow\n805: Context(\"Complete Workflow\", func() {\n806:     It(\"should execute pack -> build -> publish -> invoke workflow\", func() {\n807:         // Pack agent\n808:         // Build image\n809:         // Publish to cluster\n810:         // Invoke agent\n811:         // Verify results\n812:     })\n813: })\n814: ```\n815: \n816: #### Integration-Level E2E Tests\n817: \n818: Test interactions between different components:\n819: \n820: ```go\n821: // Test router -> workload-manager integration\n822: Context(\"Router Integration\", func() {\n823:     It(\"should route requests to workload-manager correctly\", func() {\n824:         // Create session via workload-manager\n825:         // Route request via router\n826:         // Verify routing\n827:     })\n828: })\n829: ```\n830: \n831: ### Test Parallelization\n832: \n833: ```go\n834: // Run tests in parallel\n835: var _ = Describe(\"Parallel Tests\", Ordered, func() {\n836:     BeforeAll(func() {\n837:         // Shared setup\n838:     })\n839: \n840:     Context(\"Test Group 1\", Serial, func() {\n841:         It(\"test 1\", func() {})\n842:         It(\"test 2\", func() {})\n843:     })\n844: \n845:     Context(\"Test Group 2\", Serial, func() {\n846:         It(\"test 3\", func() {})\n847:         It(\"test 4\", func() {})\n848:     })\n849: })\n850: ```\n851: \n852: ### Test Isolation\n853: \n854: ```go\n855: // Each test gets its own namespace\n856: BeforeEach(func() {\n857:     ns = fmt.Sprintf(\"e2e-%s\", strings.ToLower(randomString(8)))\n858:     \n859:     _, err := f.Clientset.CoreV1().Namespaces().Create(\n860:         context.Background(),\n861:         &corev1.Namespace{\n862:             ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n863:                 Name: ns,\n864:             },\n865:         },\n866:         metav1.CreateOptions{},\n867:     )\n868:     Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n869: })\n870: \n871: AfterEach(func() {\n872:     if !CurrentSpecReport().Failed() {\n873:         // Only cleanup on success to preserve state for debugging\n874:         f.Clientset.CoreV1().Namespaces().Delete(\n875:             context.Background(),\n876:             ns,\n877:             metav1.DeleteOptions{},\n878:         )\n879:     }\n880: })\n881: ```\n882: \n883: ### Test Data Management\n884: \n885: ```go\n886: // TestData provides test data management\n887: type TestData struct {\n888:     manifests map[string]string\n889:     configs   map[string]interface{}\n890: }\n891: \n892: // LoadManifests loads test manifests from files\n893: func (td *TestData) LoadManifests(dir string) error {\n894:     files, err := os.ReadDir(dir)\n895:     if err != nil {\n896:         return err\n897:     }\n898:     \n899:     for _, file := range files {\n900:         content, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, file.Name()))\n901:         if err != nil {\n902:             return err\n903:         }\n904:         \n905:         td.manifests[file.Name()] = string(content)\n906:     }\n907:     \n908:     return nil\n909: }\n910: \n911: // GetManifest returns a specific manifest\n912: func (td *TestData) GetManifest(name string) string {\n913:     return td.manifests[name]\n914: }\n915: ```\n916: \n917: ### Test Reporting\n918: \n919: ```go\n920: // TestReporter provides custom test reporting\n921: type TestReporter struct {\n922:     outputPath string\n923: }\n924: \n925: // Report generates a test report\n926: func (r *TestReporter) Report(report types.Report) {\n927:     reportData := struct {\n928:         Summary  types.SuiteSummary\n929:         Specs    []types.SpecReport\n930:         Duration time.Duration\n931:     }{\n932:         Summary:  report.SuiteSummary,\n933:         Specs:    report.SpecReports,\n934:         Duration: report.EndTime.Sub(report.StartTime),\n935:     }\n936:     \n937:     // Generate HTML report\n938:     r.generateHTMLReport(reportData)\n939:     \n940:     // Generate JSON report\n941:     r.generateJSONReport(reportData)\n942:     \n943:     // Generate JUnit XML report\n944:     r.generateJUnitReport(reportData)\n945: }\n946: ```\n947: \n948: ## Environment Setup\n949: \n950: ### Local Development Setup\n951: \n952: ```bash\n953: # Create kind cluster\n954: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n955: \n956: # Load Docker images\n957: kind load docker-image agentcube:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n958: kind load docker-image agentcube-workload-manager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n959: kind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n960: \n961: # Deploy AgentCube\n962: kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\n963: kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n964: \n965: # Wait for deployment\n966: kubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n967:     deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n968: \n969: # Run E2E tests\n970: go test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n971: ```\n972: \n973: ### CI/CD Integration\n974: \n975: ```yaml\n976: # .github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml\n977: name: E2E Tests\n978: \n979: on:\n980:   push:\n981:     branches: [main, develop]\n982:   pull_request:\n983:     branches: [main, develop]\n984: \n985: jobs:\n986:   e2e-tests:\n987:     name: E2E Tests\n988:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n989:     \n990:     steps:\n991:       - name: Checkout code\n992:         uses: actions/checkout@v3\n993:       \n994:       - name: Set up Go\n995:         uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n996:         with:\n997:           go-version: '1.24'\n998:       \n999:       - name: Set up kind\n1000:         uses: engineerd/setup-kind@v0.5.0\n1001:         with:\n1002:           version: v0.20.0\n1003:           image: kindest/node:v1.28.0\n1004:       \n1005:       - name: Build images\n1006:         run: |\n1007:           make docker-build\n1008:           kind load docker-image agentcube:latest\n1009:       \n1010:       - name: Deploy AgentCube\n1011:         run: |\n1012:           kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\n1013:           kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n1014:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n1015:             deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n1016:       \n1017:       - name: Run E2E tests\n1018:         run: |\n1019:           go test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -timeout 30m\n1020:       \n1021:       - name: Upload test results\n1022:         if: always()\n1023:         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3\n1024:         with:\n1025:           name: e2e-test-results\n1026:           path: test/e2e/reports/\n1027: ```\n1028: \n1029: ### Test Manifests\n1030: \n1031: **File**: `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml`\n1032: \n1033: ```yaml\n1034: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1035: kind: AgentRuntime\n1036: metadata:\n1037:   name: simple-agent\n1038:   namespace: {{ .Namespace }}\n1039: spec:\n1040:   maxSessionDuration: \"1h\"\n1041:   sessionTimeout: \"5m\"\n1042:   targetPort:\n1043:   - port: 8080\n1044:     protocol: \"HTTP\"\n1045:   podTemplate:\n1046:     spec:\n1047:       containers:\n1048:       - name: agent\n1049:         image: nginx:latest\n1050:         ports:\n1051:         - containerPort: 8080\n1052: ```\n1053: \n1054: **File**: `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml`\n1055: \n1056: ```yaml\n1057: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1058: kind: CodeInterpreter\n1059: metadata:\n1060:   name: python-interpreter\n1061:   namespace: {{ .Namespace }}\n1062: spec:\n1063:   authMode: \"picod\"\n1064:   maxSessionDuration: \"1h\"\n1065:   sessionTimeout: \"5m\"\n1066:   ports:\n1067:   - port: 8080\n1068:     protocol: \"HTTP\"\n1069:   template:\n1070:     spec:\n1071:       containers:\n1072:       - name: interpreter\n1073:         image: python:3.11-slim\n1074: ```\n1075: \n1076: ## Performance Testing\n1077: \n1078: ### Load Testing\n1079: \n1080: ```go\n1081: // LoadTest performs load testing on the system\n1082: func LoadTest(\n1083:     ctx context.Context,\n1084:     helper *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper,\n1085:     agentName string,\n1086:     concurrency int,\n1087:     duration time.Duration,\n1088: ) error {\n1089:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n1090:     errors := make(chan error, concurrency)\n1091:     \n1092:     done := make(chan struct{})\n1093:     go func() {\n1094:         time.Sleep(duration)\n1095:         close(done)\n1096:     }()\n1097:     \n1098:     for i := 0; i < concurrency; i++ {\n1099:         wg.Add(1)\n1100:         go func(id int) {\n1101:             defer wg.Done()\n1102:             \n1103:             for {\n1104:                 select {\n1105:                 case <-done:\n1106:                     return\n1107:                 default:\n1108:                     req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", agentName, helper.Namespace())\n1109:                     _, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n1110:                     errors <- err\n1111:                 }\n1112:             }\n1113:         }(i)\n1114:     }\n1115:     \n1116:     wg.Wait()\n1117:     close(errors)\n1118:     \n1119:     // Collect errors\n1120:     var allErrors []error\n1121:     for err := range errors {\n1122:         if err != nil {\n1123:             allErrors = append(allErrors, err)\n1124:         }\n1125:     }\n1126:     \n1127:     if len(allErrors) > 0 {\n1128:         return fmt.Errorf(\"load test failed with %d errors\", len(allErrors))\n1129:     }\n1130:     \n1131:     return nil\n1132: }\n1133: ```\n1134: \n1135: ### Stress Testing\n1136: \n1137: ```go\n1138: // StressTest performs stress testing by creating many resources\n1139: func StressTest(\n1140:     ctx context.Context,\n1141:     helper *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper,\n1142:     count int,\n1143: ) error {\n1144:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n1145:     errors := make(chan error, count)\n1146:     \n1147:     for i := 0; i < count; i++ {\n1148:         wg.Add(1)\n1149:         go func(id int) {\n1150:             defer wg.Done()\n1151:             \n1152:             art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(fmt.Sprintf(\"stress-agent-%d\", id))\n1153:             _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n1154:             errors <- err\n1155:         }(i)\n1156:     }\n1157:     \n1158:     wg.Wait()\n1159:     close(errors)\n1160:     \n1161:     // Verify all creations succeeded\n1162:     for err := range errors {\n1163:         if err != nil {\n1164:             return err\n1165:         }\n1166:     }\n1167:     \n1168:     return nil\n1169: }\n1170: ```\n1171: \n1172: ## Implementation Checklist\n1173: \n1174: ### Phase 1: Foundation\n1175: - [ ] Create test framework structure (`test/e2e/framework/`)\n1176: - [ ] Implement `TestFramework` with environment setup\n1177: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeHelper` with CRUD operations\n1178: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterHelper` with execution operations\n1179: - [ ] Implement custom assertions\n1180: - [ ] Create test fixtures\n1181: \n1182: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests\n1183: - [ ] Implement AgentRuntime creation tests\n1184: - [ ] Implement AgentRuntime invocation tests\n1185: - [ ] Implement AgentRuntime lifecycle tests\n1186: - [ ] Implement AgentRuntime error handling tests\n1187: - [ ] Implement AgentRuntime concurrent access tests\n1188: \n1189: ### Phase 3: CodeInterpreter Tests\n1190: - [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter creation tests\n1191: - [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter execution tests\n1192: - [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter file operations tests\n1193: - [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter error handling tests\n1194: \n1195: ### Phase 4: Integration Tests\n1196: - [ ] Implement workflow tests (pack -> build -> publish -> invoke)\n1197: - [ ] Implement routing integration tests\n1198: - [ ] Implement session management tests\n1199: - [ ] Implement scalability tests\n1200: \n1201: ### Phase 5: Test Infrastructure\n1202: - [ ] Implement test failure handler\n1203: - [ ] Implement retry logic\n1204: - [ ] Implement timeout management\n1205: - [ ] Implement test reporting\n1206: - [ ] Create test manifests\n1207: \n1208: ### Phase 6: Documentation\n1209: - [ ] Write test documentation\n1210: - [ ] Create running tests guide\n1211: - [ ] Document test patterns\n1212: - [ ] Document CI/CD integration\n1213: \n1214: ### Phase 7: Performance & Security\n1215: - [ ] Implement load testing\n1216: - [ ] Implement stress testing\n1217: - [ ] Implement security testing\n1218: - [ ] Create performance baselines\n1219: \n1220: ## References\n1221: \n1222: - [Ginkgo Testing Framework](https://onsi.github.io/ginkgo/)\n1223: - [Gomega Matchers Library](https://onsi.github.io/gomega/)\n1224: - [kind (Kubernetes in Docker)](https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/)\n1225: - [client-go Documentation](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n1226: - [AgentCube Project](../../README.md)\n1227: - [client-go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n1228: - [Workload Manager Design](../../pkg/workloadmanager/design-testing.md)\n\n(End of file - total 1228 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the technical implementation of comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube project. The E2E test suite validates the complete system behavior by deploying a real or simulated Kubernetes environment, creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, and verifying end-to-end workflows including session creation, invocation, routing, and lifecycle management.\n\n**Module:** `test/e2e`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Source Root:** `/test/e2e/`  \n**Size:** L  \n**Dependencies:** client-go, kind/minikube/k3s, Ginkgo/Gomega\n\n## Architecture\n\n### E2E Test Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    E2E Test Framework                       │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md","time":{"start":1775896504509,"end":1775896504548}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775896504592,"sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","part":{"id":"prt_d7bae28e8001jHEte9lygTqhD7","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7bae133b001U1q8ONuj1CXdnU","sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":15847,"input":15750,"output":97,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775896509237,"sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","part":{"id":"prt_d7bae3b32001FfwfFceef0B6qY","messageID":"msg_d7bae2930001yB646b4i10al1V","sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896606049,"sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","part":{"id":"prt_d7bafb4e3001srJviVcjGc0CLA","messageID":"msg_d7bae2930001yB646b4i10al1V","sessionID":"ses_28451fe34ffeWA1DwLqUewwglS","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-288df2f72b504807aef65c75e2733b6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Task Checklist\n\n## Overview\n\nThis task checklist breaks down the implementation of E2E integration tests for the AgentCube project into atomic, independently verifiable tasks.\n\n**Module:** `test/e2e`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n**Status:** Ready for Implementation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Framework Infrastructure)\n\n### 1.1 Create Test Framework Structure\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.1  \n**Description:** Create directory structure and package initialization for E2E test framework\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Directory `test/e2e/framework/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/agentruntime/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/codeinterpreter/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/integration/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/manifests/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/` exists\n- Directory `test/e2e/manifests/deployments/` exists\n- All directories contain `go.mod` package declaration `package e2e` or `package framework`\n- `go build ./test/e2e/...` succeeds without errors\n\n**Dependencies:** None  \n**Estimated Time:** 30 minutes\n\n---\n\n### 1.2 Implement TestFramework Core\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.2  \n**Description:** Implement core TestFramework struct with Kubernetes client initialization\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/framework.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `TestFramework` struct exists with fields: config, clientset, agentClient, namespace, clusterName, httpClient, cleanup\n- `FrameworkOptions` struct exists with configurable options\n- `NewDefaultFramework(name string) *TestFramework` function works and returns framework with defaults\n- `NewFramework(name string, opts FrameworkOptions) *TestFramework` function works and accepts custom options\n- Default namespace format is `e2e-test-<random>` when not specified\n- Default timeout is 5 minutes when not specified\n- Default poll interval is 1 second when not specified\n- `go test -c ./test/e2e/framework/` compiles successfully\n- Unit tests verify framework initialization with various options\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.1  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 1.3 Implement Kubernetes Environment Setup\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.3  \n**Description:** Add Kubernetes environment setup and teardown methods to TestFramework\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/framework.go` (extend)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `AgentCubeReady() bool` method checks if AgentCube deployment is ready\n- `Setup() error` method creates test namespace if needed\n- `Cleanup() error` method deletes test namespace and registered cleanup functions\n- `Namespace() string` method returns current test namespace\n- `Clientset() *kubernetes.Clientset` method returns Kubernetes client\n- `AgentClient() *agentclient.Clientset` method returns AgentCube client\n- Cleanup functions are executed in reverse order\n- Setup creates namespace with random suffix if not specified\n- Cleanup respects `SkipCleanup` option\n- Unit tests verify setup/teardown behavior\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 1.4 Implement AgentRuntimeHelper\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.4  \n**Description:** Implement helper utilities for AgentRuntime CRUD operations\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `AgentRuntimeHelper` struct exists with framework reference\n- `NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f *TestFramework) *AgentRuntimeHelper` constructor works\n- `CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, agent) (*AgentRuntime, error)` creates AgentRuntime resource\n- `GetAgentRuntime(ctx, name) (*AgentRuntime, error)` retrieves AgentRuntime by name\n- `WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, name, timeout) error` waits until AgentRuntime is ready\n- `CreateSession(ctx, req) (*CreateSandboxResponse, error)` creates session via workload-manager\n- `InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, headers) (*InvokeResponse, error)` invokes session\n- `DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID) error` deletes session\n- All methods handle context cancellation properly\n- Unit tests verify each helper method\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.3  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 1.5 Implement CodeInterpreterHelper\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.5  \n**Description:** Implement helper utilities for CodeInterpreter operations\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go` (extend)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `CodeInterpreterHelper` struct exists with framework reference\n- `NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f *TestFramework) *CodeInterpreterHelper` constructor works\n- `CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci) (*CodeInterpreter, error)` creates CodeInterpreter resource\n- `GetCodeInterpreter(ctx, name) (*CodeInterpreter, error)` retrieves CodeInterpreter by name\n- `WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, name, timeout) error` waits until CodeInterpreter is ready\n- `ExecuteCode(ctx, sessionID, code) (*ExecuteResponse, error)` executes code in session\n- `UploadFile(ctx, sessionID, filename, content) error` uploads file to session\n- `DownloadFile(ctx, sessionID, filename) ([]byte, error)` downloads file from session\n- All methods handle context cancellation properly\n- Unit tests verify each helper method\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.3  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 1.6 Implement Custom Assertions\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.6  \n**Description:** Implement custom Gomega matchers for common assertions\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/assertions.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `EventuallyWithTimeout(actual, timeout, intervals) AsyncAssertion` wrapper exists\n- `ConsistentlyWithTimeout(actual, timeout, intervals) AsyncAssertion` wrapper exists\n- `HaveConditions(expected...) OmegaMatcher` verifies resource conditions\n- `BeReady() OmegaMatcher` verifies resource Ready status is true\n- `HavePhase(phase) OmegaMatcher` verifies resource phase matches\n- `HaveEndpoint(endpoint) OmegaMatcher` verifies service endpoint exists\n- `ReturnSuccess() OmegaMatcher` verifies HTTP 2xx response\n- `ReturnStatusCode(code) OmegaMatcher` verifies specific HTTP status code\n- `HaveSessionID() OmegaMatcher` verifies response contains session ID\n- All matchers have descriptive failure messages\n- Unit tests verify each matcher behavior\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 1.7 Create Test Fixtures\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.7  \n**Description:** Implement fixture generators for test resources\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/fixtures.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `NewTestAgentRuntime(name) *AgentRuntime` creates AgentRuntime with minimal valid spec\n- `NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec(name, spec) *AgentRuntime` creates AgentRuntime with custom spec\n- `NewTestCodeInterpreter(name) *CodeInterpreter` creates CodeInterpreter with minimal valid spec\n- `NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec(name, spec) *CodeInterpreter` creates CodeInterpreter with custom spec\n- `NewTestSessionRequest(kind, name, namespace) *CreateSandboxRequest` creates session request\n- `NewTestInvokePayload(data map[string]interface{}) []byte` creates JSON payload\n- Fixtures use sensible defaults (e.g., nginx:latest for container image)\n- Fixtures include required fields for resource creation\n- Unit tests verify fixture generation\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.4, T-1.5  \n**Estimated Time:** 1.5 hours\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests\n\n### 2.1 Implement AgentRuntime Test Suite\n\n**Task ID:** T-2.1  \n**Description:** Create main AgentRuntime E2E test suite with Ginkgo\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/agentruntime_suite_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Test suite file exists with proper package declaration\n- `Describe(\"AgentRuntime E2E\", func() { ... })` top-level describe block\n- `BeforeSuite` initializes framework and waits for AgentCube to be ready\n- `AfterSuite` performs cleanup unless `SkipCleanup` is enabled\n- Framework and helper variables declared at suite level\n- Namespace variable declared at suite level\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/` runs without errors\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -ginkgo.v` shows suite structure\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.7  \n**Estimated Time:** 1 hour\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 Implement AgentRuntime Creation Tests\n\n**Task ID:** T-2.2  \n**Description:** Implement tests for AgentRuntime creation workflows\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/creation_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Context(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() { ... })` context block\n- `It(\"should create AgentRuntime successfully\")` verifies creation succeeds\n- `It(\"should apply default values\")` verifies defaults (MaxSessionDuration: 8h, SessionTimeout: 15m)\n- `It(\"should become ready\")` verifies Ready status becomes true\n- Tests verify Name and Namespace are set correctly\n- Tests verify default values are applied\n- Tests verify status transitions to Ready\n- All tests have appropriate timeouts\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -run AgentRuntimeCreation` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-2.1  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 Implement AgentRuntime Invocation Tests\n\n**Task ID:** T-2.3  \n**Description:** Implement tests for AgentRuntime session invocation workflows\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/invocation_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Context(\"AgentRuntime Invocation\", func() { ... })` context block\n- `BeforeEach` creates AgentRuntime and waits for ready\n- `It(\"should create session successfully\")` verifies session creation returns session ID\n- `It(\"should invoke session successfully\")` verifies invocation returns 200 status\n- `It(\"should handle concurrent invocations\")` verifies 10 concurrent invocations all succeed\n- Tests verify session ID is non-empty\n- Tests verify invoke response contains expected data\n- Tests use goroutines and sync.WaitGroup for concurrency\n- Tests have appropriate timeouts\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -run AgentRuntimeInvocation` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-2.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 2.5 hours\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 Implement AgentRuntime Lifecycle Tests\n\n**Task ID:** T-2.4  \n**Description:** Implement tests for AgentRuntime lifecycle management\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/lifecycle_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Context(\"AgentRuntime Lifecycle\", func() { ... })` context block\n- `It(\"should handle session expiration\")` verifies expired session cannot be invoked\n- `It(\"should delete session successfully\")` verifies deleted session cannot be invoked\n- Expiration test uses short timeout (30s) and waits 35s\n- Deletion test invokes session, deletes, then verifies deletion\n- Tests verify error is returned for expired/deleted sessions\n- Tests have appropriate timeouts\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -run AgentRuntimeLifecycle` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-2.3  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 Implement AgentRuntime Error Handling Tests\n\n**Task ID:** T-2.5  \n**Description:** Implement tests for AgentRuntime error scenarios\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/error_handling_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Context(\"AgentRuntime Error Handling\", func() { ... })` context block\n- `It(\"should reject invalid spec\")` verifies invalid spec returns error\n- `It(\"should reject non-existent session invocation\")` verifies error for missing session\n- `It(\"should handle malformed payload\")` verifies error handling for bad payload\n- `It(\"should handle timeout\")` verifies timeout error\n- Tests verify appropriate error messages\n- Tests verify error codes\n- Tests have appropriate timeouts\n- `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -run AgentRuntimeErrorHandling