llects status of all AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n- `collectEvents(spec)` collects Kubernetes events for namespace\n- `saveDiagnostics(spec)` saves diagnostics to `test/e2e/reports/diagnostics/` directory\n- Each test failure generates:\n  - Pod logs file: `<test-name>-<pod-name>.log`\n  - Resource status file: `<test-name>-resources.json`\n  - Events file: `<test-name>-events.json`\n- Handler is registered with Ginkgo in test suites\n- Diagnostics are saved even when test crashes\n- `go test ./test/e2e/... -ginkgo.v` generates diagnostics on failures\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.7  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 5.2 Implement Retry Logic Utilities\n\n**Task ID:** T-5.2  \n**Description:** Implement retry utilities for flaky operations\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/retry.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Retryable(fn, maxRetries, backoff) error` function exists\n- Retryable implements exponential backoff with jitter\n- Retryable returns last error on failure\n- `EventuallyRetryable(actual, timeout, pollingInterval, maxRetries)` wrapper exists\n- Retryable respects context cancellation\n- Unit tests verify retry behavior\n- Unit tests verify backoff calculation\n- Integration test uses Retryable for known flaky operation\n- `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Retry` passes\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.6  \n**Estimated Time:** 1.5 hours\n\n---\n\n### 5.3 Implement Timeout Management Utilities\n\n**Task ID:** T-5.3  \n**Description:** Implement timeout context utilities for test operations\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/timeout.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `TimeoutContext(timeout) (ctx, cancel)` function exists\n- `WithDefaultTimeout() (ctx, cancel)` function exists (5 minute default)\n- Timeout contexts log when timeout occurs\n- Cancel functions clean up resources properly\n- Timeout contexts handle nested timeouts correctly\n- Unit tests verify timeout behavior\n- Unit tests verify cancellation behavior\n- Integration test demonstrates timeout handling\n- `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Timeout` passes\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 1 hour\n\n---\n\n### 5.4 Implement Test Reporting\n\n**Task ID:** T-5.4  \n**Description:** Implement custom test reporting with multiple output formats\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/framework/reporting.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `TestReporter` struct exists with outputPath field\n- `Report(report)` method exists\n- `generateHTMLReport(reportData)` generates HTML report\n- `generateJSONReport(reportData)` generates JSON report\n- `generateJUnitReport(reportData)` generates JUnit XML report\n- Reports include: summary, specs, duration, pass/fail counts\n- Reports are saved to `test/e2e/reports/` directory\n- HTML report is human-readable with filtering\n- JSON report is machine-readable\n- JUnit report is CI/CD compatible\n- Reporter is registered with Ginkgo\n- `go test ./test/e2e/... -ginkgo.report` generates all reports\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 5.5 Create Test Manifests\n\n**Task ID:** T-5.5  \n**Description:** Create test manifest YAML files for test resources\n\n**Files:**\n- `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml`\n- `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/multi-container-agent.yaml`\n- `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml`\n- `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/node-interpreter.yaml`\n- `test/e2e/manifests/deployments/agentcube-minimal.yaml`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- All manifests use template syntax for namespace `{{ .Namespace }}`\n- All manifests are valid Kubernetes YAML\n- All manifests are valid AgentCube CRDs\n- `simple-agent.yaml` creates minimal AgentRuntime with nginx\n- `multi-container-agent.yaml` creates AgentRuntime with 2 containers\n- `python-interpreter.yaml` creates CodeInterpreter with Python 3.11\n- `node-interpreter.yaml` creates CodeInterpreter with Node.js\n- `agentcube-minimal.yaml` is minimal AgentCube deployment\n- `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml` works (with namespace substitution)\n- `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml` works (with namespace substitution)\n\n**Dependencies:** T-1.7  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Documentation\n\n### 6.1 Write E2E Test Documentation\n\n**Task ID:** T-6.1  \n**Description:** Create comprehensive documentation for E2E test suite\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/README.md`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- README exists with:\n  - Overview of E2E test suite\n  - Prerequisites (Go, kind/k3s, kubectl, Docker)\n  - Installation instructions\n  - Architecture diagram (from design.md)\n  - Running tests locally (kind setup, load images, deploy, run tests)\n  - Running tests in CI/CD (GitHub Actions workflow reference)\n  - Test organization (directory structure, test categories)\n  - Writing new tests (patterns, helpers, assertions)\n  - Debugging failed tests (diagnostics, logs)\n  - Performance testing (load tests, stress tests)\n- All code blocks are copy-pasteable and work\n- All file paths are correct\n- All commands are tested and verified\n- `test -f test/e2e/README.md` succeeds\n\n**Dependencies:** T-5.5  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 6.2 Create Running Tests Guide\n\n**Task ID:** T-6.2  \n**Description:** Create detailed step-by-step guide for running E2E tests\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- RUNNING_TESTS.md exists with:\n  - Local development setup (kind cluster creation, image loading, deployment)\n  - Quick start (single command to run all tests)\n  - Running specific test suites (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Integration)\n  - Running specific tests (Ginkgo focus filter)\n  - Running tests with options (verbose, parallel, skip cleanup)\n  - Running tests with race detector\n  - Running tests with coverage\n  - Troubleshooting common issues (cluster not ready, image not found, timeout)\n  - Interpreting test results (reading reports, understanding failures)\n- All commands are copy-pasteable and work\n- All file paths are correct\n- All commands are tested and verified\n- `test -f test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md` succeeds\n\n**Dependencies:** T-6.1  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 6.3 Document Test Patterns\n\n**Task ID:** T-6.3  \n**Description:** Document common test patterns and best practices\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/PATTERNS.md`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- PATTERNS.md exists with:\n  - Test structure patterns (Describe/Context/It hierarchy)\n  - Setup/teardown patterns (BeforeSuite/AfterSuite, BeforeEach/AfterEach)\n  - Assertion patterns (custom assertions, matchers)\n  - Helper usage patterns (agent runtime helper, code interpreter helper)\n  - Fixture usage patterns (resource fixtures, payload fixtures)\n  - Error handling patterns (error verification, timeout handling)\n  - Concurrency patterns (goroutines, WaitGroup, channels)\n  - Isolation patterns (per-test namespaces, resource cleanup)\n  - Retry patterns (Retryable, EventuallyRetryable)\n  - Each pattern includes:\n    - Description\n    - When to use\n    - Example code\n    - Common pitfalls\n- All code examples are valid and tested\n- All file paths are correct\n- `test -f test/e2e/PATTERNS.md` succeeds\n\n**Dependencies:** T-6.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n### 6.4 Document CI/CD Integration\n\n**Task ID:** T-6.4  \n**Description:** Create CI/CD workflow for running E2E tests\n\n**File:** `.github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- GitHub Actions workflow exists with:\n  - Trigger conditions (push to main/develop, pull request)\n  - Job setup (checkout, Go setup, kind setup)\n  - Build step (docker build, kind load)\n  - Deploy step (apply CRDs, apply deployment, wait for ready)\n  - Test step (run E2E tests with timeout)\n  - Upload artifacts step (upload test results, reports, diagnostics)\n  - Cleanup step (delete cluster)\n- Workflow runs successfully on GitHub Actions\n- Workflow uploads artifacts on both success and failure\n- Workflow runs all E2E tests\n- Workflow completes within 45 minutes\n- `test -f .github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml` succeeds\n\n**Dependencies:** T-6.3  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Performance & Security\n\n### 7.1 Implement Load Testing\n\n**Task ID:** T-7.1  \n**Description:** Implement load testing utilities and tests\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/integration/load_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `LoadTest(ctx, helper, agentName, concurrency, duration) error` function exists\n- LoadTest creates concurrent sessions for specified duration\n- LoadTest collects errors and metrics\n- LoadTest measures throughput (requests/second)\n- LoadTest measures latency (p50, p95, p99)\n- LoadTest measures error rate\n- `It(\"should handle 100 concurrent invocations for 5 minutes\")` test exists\n- Test verifies error rate < 1%\n- Test verifies p95 latency < 1s\n- Test logs performance metrics\n- Test has appropriate timeout (10 minutes)\n- `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Load` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-4.4  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 7.2 Implement Stress Testing\n\n**Task ID:** T-7.2  \n**Description:** Implement stress testing utilities and tests\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/integration/stress_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `StressTest(ctx, helper, count) error` function exists\n- StressTest creates many resources concurrently\n- StressTest creates many sessions concurrently\n- StressTest measures resource creation time\n- StressTest measures memory usage\n- StressTest measures CPU usage\n- `It(\"should handle 100 concurrent AgentRuntime creations\")` test exists\n- `It(\"should handle 1000 concurrent session creations\")` test exists\n- Tests verify system doesn't crash under stress\n- Tests verify graceful degradation\n- Tests log resource metrics\n- Tests have appropriate timeouts (15 minutes)\n- `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Stress` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-7.1  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 7.3 Implement Security Testing\n\n**Task ID:** T-7.3  \n**Description:** Implement security-focused E2E tests\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/integration/security_test.go`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `Describe(\"Security\", func() { ... })` describe block\n- `BeforeSuite` initializes framework and waits for AgentCube to be ready\n- `It(\"should reject unauthorized session creation\")` verifies auth enforcement\n- `It(\"should reject unauthorized session invocation\")` verifies auth enforcement\n- `It(\"should isolate sessions by namespace\")` verifies namespace isolation\n- `It(\"should not leak data between sessions\")` verifies session isolation\n- `It(\"should handle malicious payloads\")` verifies input validation\n- `It(\"should enforce resource quotas\")` verifies quota enforcement\n- Tests verify authentication failures\n- Tests verify authorization failures\n- Tests verify isolation boundaries\n- Tests verify input sanitization\n- Tests verify quota limits\n- Tests have appropriate timeouts\n- `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Security` passes with valid deployment\n\n**Dependencies:** T-7.2  \n**Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n\n---\n\n### 7.4 Create Performance Baselines\n\n**Task ID:** T-7.4  \n**Description:** Establish and document performance baselines\n\n**File:** `test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- BENCHMARKS.md exists with:\n  - Session creation latency baseline (target: < 2s p95)\n  - Session invocation latency baseline (target: < 100ms p95)\n  - Concurrent session throughput baseline (target: > 100 sessions/sec)\n  - AgentRuntime creation time baseline (target: < 30s)\n  - CodeInterpreter execution time baseline (target: < 500ms for simple code)\n  - Resource usage baselines (CPU, memory, network)\n  - Load testing thresholds (concurrency, duration, error rate)\n  - Stress testing thresholds (resource count, session count)\n  - How to run benchmarks\n  - How to compare against baselines\n- All baselines are measured and documented\n- All baselines include measurement methodology\n- All baselines include acceptable ranges\n- `test -f test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md` succeeds\n- `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Benchmarks` generates baseline metrics\n\n**Dependencies:** T-7.3  \n**Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n\n---\n\n## Verification Criteria\n\n### Completion Checklist\n\n- [ ] All Phase 1 tasks (T-1.1 through T-1.7) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 2 tasks (T-2.1 through T-2.6) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 3 tasks (T-3.1 through T-3.5) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 4 tasks (T-4.1 through T-4.4) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 5 tasks (T-5.1 through T-5.5) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 6 tasks (T-6.1 through T-6.4) are completed\n- [ ] All Phase 7 tasks (T-7.1 through T-7.4) are completed\n\n### Integration Testing\n\n- [ ] `go build ./test/e2e/...` succeeds without errors\n- [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/framework/...` passes all unit tests\n- [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n- [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n- [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/integration/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n- [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n- [ ] `go test -race ./test/e2e/...` passes all tests without race conditions\n- [ ] `go test -cover ./test/e2e/...` achieves > 80% code coverage\n\n### Documentation Verification\n\n- [ ] `test/e2e/README.md` exists and is complete\n- [ ] `test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md` exists and is complete\n- [ ] `test/e2e/PATTERNS.md` exists and is complete\n- [ ] `test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md` exists and is complete\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml` exists and runs successfully on GitHub Actions\n\n### Smoke Tests\n\n- [ ] E2E test suite runs successfully in kind cluster\n- [ ] E2E test suite generates test reports\n- [ ] E2E test suite collects diagnostics on failures\n- [ ] E2E test suite completes within 30 minutes\n- [ ] E2E test suite achieves acceptable performance (meets baselines)\n\n---\n\n## Total Estimated Time\n\n- Phase 1: Foundation - 13 hours\n- Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests - 13.5 hours\n- Phase 3: CodeInterpreter Tests - 12 hours\n- Phase 4: Integration Tests - 12.5 hours\n- Phase 5: Test Infrastructure - 10.5 hours\n- Phase 6: Documentation - 9 hours\n- Phase 7: Performance & Security - 11 hours\n\n**Total: 81.5 hours**\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n1. All tasks should be completed sequentially within each phase\n2. Tasks in different phases can be completed in parallel if dependencies are met\n3. Each task must pass its acceptance criteria before marking as complete\n4. Integration tests require a valid AgentCube deployment in a Kubernetes cluster\n5. Performance tests (Phase 7) should be run on dedicated hardware for accurate results\n6. Security tests (T-7.3) require understanding of AgentCube security model\n7. CI/CD integration (T-6.4) should be tested on a real GitHub repository","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775896606032,"end":1775896606044}}}}
